title: Wildlife Disease News Digest - published by the NBII Wildlife Disease Information Node
name: Wildlife Disease News Digest - published by the NBII Wildlife Disease Information Node
description: Displays the last 45 days of Global Wildlife Disease News collected by the NBII Wildlife Disease Information Node

properties.name: 125 pilot whales die in New Zealand; 43 saved
properties.description: Published by MSNBC - www.msnbc.msn.com on 12/27/2009 - Some 125 pilot whales died in New Zealand after stranding on the beach over the weekend â€” but vacationers and conservation workers Sunday managed to coax 43 others back out to sea.

properties.name: 5 more bighorns killed in effort to stop pneumonia outbreak
properties.description: Published by Billings Gazette - www.billingsgazette.net on 1/16/2010 - State wildlife officials killed five more sick bighorn sheep in West Riverside on Friday, and planned to continue attempts to stop a disease outbreak through the weekend.

properties.name: 9 rescued turtles die after Texas cold snap
properties.description: Published by Dallas Morning News - www.dallasnews.com on 1/12/2010 - Nine sea turtles rescued from the cold along the Gulf of Mexico have died as dozens of others are cared for at the Texas State Aquarium and a rehab site.

properties.name: After 6 more sheep put down, biologists likely done culling herd hit by pneumonia
properties.description: Published by The Missoulian - www.missoulian.com on 12/22/2009 - Biologists and volunteers shot six more bighorns in the East Fork of the Bitterroot this week during what will probably be the last large push to cull sick sheep from the beleaguered herd.

properties.name: Avian influenza (01): China (HK) wild bird, OIE
properties.description: Published by ProMED Mail - www.promedmail.org on 1/5/2010 - Information received on (and dated) 5 Jan 2010 from Dr Thomas Sit, Assistant Director, Inspection & Quarantine, Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department, Cheung Sha Wan, Hong Kong, Hong Kong (PR China)

properties.name: Beached beaked whale dies in Florida
properties.description: Published by United Press International - www.upi.com on 1/27/2010 - A beaked whale that beached itself in Brevard County, Fla., died despite attempts by local residents to save it, a marine expert said.

properties.name: Big decision on bighorns
properties.description: Published by Yakima Herald-Republic - www.yakima-herald.com on 12/29/2009 - Since the first week of December, about 10 bighorns on the west side of the canyon have died from pneumonia and dozens more have become infected.

properties.name: Bird flu scare in Kaziranga, birds found dead
properties.description: Published by Little About - www.littleabout.com on 1/8/2010 - A bird flu scare has hit the Kaziranga National Park in Assam with carcasses of at least a dozen migratory Bar-headed Geese found in the sanctuary, officials said Friday.

properties.name: Birds rescued after Manchester Ship Canal oil spill
properties.description: Published by BBC News - news.bbc.co.uk on 1/20/2010 - RSPCA officers are attempting to catch geese and ducks covered in oil after a spill on the Manchester Ship Canal.

properties.name: Cholera killed 2,000 birds
properties.description: Published by Amarillo.com - www.amarillo.com on 12/30/2009 - Experts have confirmed the cause of death of more than 2,000 migratory birds near Dalhart earlier this month.

properties.name: Chronic Wasting Disease Found in White-tailed Deer in Virginia
properties.description: Published by Virginia Department of Game and Inland Fisheries on 1/20/2010 - The Virginia Department of Game and Inland Fisheries (VDGIF) received laboratory confirmation on January 19, 2010, that a white-tailed deer tested positive for chronic wasting disease (CWD).

properties.name: City awaits ministry approval to trap diseased Greenboro coyote
properties.description: Published by Ottawa Citizen - www.ottawacitizen.com on 2/1/2010 - ... The coyote is believed to have mange, a skin disease caused by parasitic mites.

properties.name: Cold killed record number of sea turtles
properties.description: Published by Herald Tribune - www.heraldtribune.com on 1/22/2010 - Volunteers, state biologists and conservation groups across Florida mounted an unprecedented rescue effort to save most of the 5,000 endangered sea turtles found near death during this month's cold snap.

properties.name: Cold snap killing fish at alarming rate
properties.description: Published by Miami Herald - www.miamiherald.com on 1/20/2010 - Waters all around Florida are about to get very stinky the next few days as hundreds of thousands of fish killed by the recent and extended cold weather begin to decompose and float to the surface.

properties.name: Crews try to protect wildlife from Texas spill
properties.description: Published by San Francisco Chronicle - www.sfgate.com on 1/25/2010 - Crews worked Sunday to protect two sensitive wildlife areas after a large crude oil spill shut down parts of a major southeast Texas port, state Land Commissioner Jerry Patterson said.

properties.name: Dead whale reported floating near Whidbey Navy base
properties.description: Published by Whidbey News Times - www.seattlepi.com on 1/9/2010 - A dead whale was seen floating near Whidbey Island Thursday.

properties.name: Dolphin washes up on Cabrillo Beach
properties.description: Published by The Daily Breeze - www.dailybreeze.com on 1/22/2010 - A 7-foot-long Risso's dolphin that came ashore Friday at Cabrillo Beach is the latest in a series of dead marine mammals to wash up possibly as a result of this week's powerful rainstorms.

properties.name: Dozens of disoriented pelicans recovering from storm's effects
properties.description: Published by The Daily Breeze - www.dailybreeze.com on 1/21/2010 - A few dozen very wet, skinny California brown pelicans huddled by heaters at the International Bird Rescue Research Center in San Pedro on Thursday.

properties.name: Dozens of native birds die in WA's south
properties.description: Published by Sydney Morning Herald - www.smh.com.au on 1/8/2010 - Record temperatures are being blamed for the deaths of scores of birds in Western Australia's south.

properties.name: Dozens of native birds die in WA's south
properties.description: Published by Sydney Morning Herald - www.smh.com.au on 1/8/2010 - Record temperatures are being blamed for the deaths of scores of birds in Western Australia's south.

properties.name: FWC records unprecedented number of cold-related manatee deaths
properties.description: Published by Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission on 1/26/2010 - The cold period that began Jan. 2 and lasted nearly two weeks continues to impact Florida manatees.

properties.name: FWP kills 7 sheep with pneumona
properties.description: Published by Billings Gazette - www.billingsgazette.net on 1/14/2010 - State wildlife officials have killed seven bighorn sheep as they try to limit an outbreak of pneumonia in a herd in the mountains west of the Marshall Ski Area.

properties.name: Frigid Gulf water creating fish kills
properties.description: Published by My Fox Tampa Bay - www.myfoxtampabay.com on 1/11/2010 - Salt water fish have taken a big hit from the recent cold spell. Dozens of fish kills have been reported to the state fish and wildlife commission, from all over the state.

properties.name: G&F sends four elk to slaughter
properties.description: Published by Casper Star-Tribune - www.trib.com on 1/26/2010 - Four elk captured over the weekend and tested for brucellosis had positive test results and were sent to slaughter Monday morning, according to Wyoming Game and Fish Department public information specialist Mark Gocke.

properties.name: Gulls' death attributed to bacterial infection
properties.description: Published by Gulf News - www.gulfnews.com on 1/31/2010 - Gulls have a few places between which to move in the area and depend on food thrown away or dead plants and animals, which can cause botulism, a bacterial disease associated with birds.

properties.name: Hantavirus blamed for Alamosa death
properties.description: Published by Denver Post - www.denverpost.com on 1/28/2010 - A virus carried by deer mice is being blamed for the death of an Alamosa County person.

properties.name: Hong Kong: Oriental Magpie Robin tested for H5 virus
properties.description: Published by Web Newswire - www.webnewswire.com on 1/1/2010 - Preliminary testing of a dead Oriental Magpie Robin found in Hok Tau, Pat Sin Leng had indicated a suspected case of H5 avian influenza, a spokesman for the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department (AFCD) said today (December 31), adding that further confirmatory tests were being conducted.

properties.name: Official: Dolphins, pelicans found dead
properties.description: Published by Fox News 10 WALA - www.fox10tv.com on 1/5/2010 - Almost two dozen dolphins and pelicans are found dead in Baldwin County and researchers don't know why.

properties.name: Oregon pelicans face starvation
properties.description: Published by Mail Tribune - www.mailtribune.com on 1/27/2010 - California brown pelicans now stranded along the Oregon Coast are starving by the hundreds and begging for food instead of migrating south in what is seen as a rare and somewhat macabre phenomenon.

properties.name: Pearl Beach bird deaths natural phenomenon
properties.description: Published by Coast News - www.thecoastnews.com on 1/13/2010 - Gosford City Council has investigated reports of multiple bird deaths within the Pearl Beach Lagoon and it has been found that the affected birds demonstrated clinical signs of being infected with a naturally occurring avian disease.

properties.name: Pelicans found dead during cold snap suffered in final days
properties.description: Published by Alabama Live - www.al.com on 1/26/2010 - Autopsy results from a handful of the 100-plus sea birds found dead on Dauphin Island and the Fort Morgan peninsula during the recent cold snap paint a picture of the animals' bleak final days.

properties.name: Pneumonia Confirmed In Lower Rock Creek Bighorn Sheep
properties.description: Published by Montana Fish, Wildlife & Parks - fwp.mt.gov/news on 1/26/2010 - Montana Fish, Wildlife & Parks (FWP) announced today that a pneumonia outbreak is underway in another bighorn sheep population in west-central Montana.

properties.name: Pneumonia outbreak widens; FWP will kill 95 sheep in West Riverside herd
properties.description: Published by The Missoulian - www.missoulian.com on 1/22/2010 - The deadly pneumonia outbreak in West Riverside's bighorn sheep herd has spread, prompting wildlife officials to increase the number of animals to be culled.

properties.name: Rabid Raccoons Continue to Invade Central Park, Eight More Found in Two Weeks  Read more: http://www.dnainfo.com/20100120/central-park/rabid-raccoons-continue-invade-central-park-eight-more-found-two-weeks#ixzz0dBgcfdWC
properties.description: Published by DNAinfo - www.dnainfo.com on 1/20/2010 - Rabid raccoons have been increasingly infesting Central Park with eight of the mad animals found there in the past two weeks, according to the Department of Health.

properties.name: Rabies Alert Issued For Middleburg
properties.description: Published by News 4 Jax.com - www.news4jax.com on 2/1/2010 - The Clay County Health Department has issued a rabies alert for the Middleburg... The alert is in response to a raccoon that recently tested positive for rabies, according to the health department.

properties.name: Salt Plains refuge personnel to scare off sandhill cranes with propane cannons
properties.description: Published by Enid News - enidnews.com on 1/28/2009 - U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service personnel from Salt Plains National Wildlife Refuge have set up propane cannons to scare sandhill cranes away from fields where more than 150 of the birds have died after eating moldy peanuts.

properties.name: Sea turtle update: Mote treating cold-stunned sea turtles
properties.description: Published by Cape Coral Daily Breeze - www.cape-coral-daily-breeze.com on 1/11/2010 - Cold water temperatures are affecting hundreds of animals statewide, including sea turtles, and several have arrived at Mote Marine Laboratory for treatment.

properties.name: Sea turtle update: Mote treating cold-stunned sea turtles
properties.description: Published by Cape Coral Daily Breeze - www.cape-coral-daily-breeze.com on 1/11/2010 - Cold water temperatures are affecting hundreds of animals statewide, including sea turtles, and several have arrived at Mote Marine Laboratory for treatment.

properties.name: Sea turtle update: Mote treating cold-stunned sea turtles
properties.description: Published by Cape Coral Daily Breeze - www.cape-coral-daily-breeze.com on 1/11/2010 - Cold water temperatures are affecting hundreds of animals statewide, including sea turtles, and several have arrived at Mote Marine Laboratory for treatment.

properties.name: Sixteen New CWD Cases Found in Hampshire County
properties.description: Published by MetroNews - www.wvmetronews.com on 1/16/2010 - DNR Biologists report 16 deer killed by hunters in the 2009 deer season tested positive for the presence of CWD.

properties.name: Stunned Sea Turtles Rescued From Cold
properties.description: Published by Central Florida News13 - www.cfnews13.com on 1/12/2010 - More than 1,000 sea turtles across the state have been stunned by the cold, sending wildlife groups scrambling to help them out.

properties.name: Stunned Sea Turtles Rescued From Cold
properties.description: Published by Central Florida News13 - www.cfnews13.com on 1/12/2010 - More than 1,000 sea turtles across the state have been stunned by the cold, sending wildlife groups scrambling to help them out.

properties.name: Testing for Chronic Wasting Disease in Early Stages
properties.description: Published by Kansas City InfoZine - www.infozine.com on 1/4/2010 - Testing for chronic wasting disease (CWD) in samples collected from deer taken during the 2009 season is only about one-third complete, but the Kansas Department of Wildlife and Parks (KDWP) reports that six samples have shown presumptive positive.

properties.name: Testing for Chronic Wasting Disease in Early Stages
properties.description: Published by Kansas City InfoZine - www.infozine.com on 1/4/2010 - Testing for chronic wasting disease (CWD) in samples collected from deer taken during the 2009 season is only about one-third complete, but the Kansas Department of Wildlife and Parks (KDWP) reports that six samples have shown presumptive positive.

properties.name: Tests after whale's death on Northumberland coast
properties.description: Published by BBC News - news.bbc.co.uk on 1/26/2010 - A post-mortem examination is due to be carried out on a sperm whale which died after becoming stranded on rocks on the Northumberland coast.

properties.name: Turtles dying en masse on Odisha coast
properties.description: Published by Kalinga Times - www.kalingatimes.com on 1/5/2009 - The sighting of bloated and motionless bodies of Oilve Ridley sea turtles lends credence to belief that unlawful trawling operation despite prohibition is in full swing along the Gahirmatha marine sanctuary.

properties.name: Whale common in tropical waters turns up dead in Puget Sound
properties.description: Published by Times Colonist - www.timescolonist.com on 1/21/2010 - The body of a Bryde's whale, an animal usually found in warm tropical waters, washed up the a beach near Olympia, Wash., this week and U.S. and Canadian scientists are studying tissue samples to figure out why the whale strayed so far north.

properties.name: What's killing the ducks of Hedgeley Dene?
properties.description: Published by The Age - theage.com.au on 1/20/2010 - An investigation into the picturesque Glen Iris locale is under way at the Department of Primary Industries, after a large number of bird deaths in recent days.

properties.name: Wild deer disease surveillance continues; new bovine TB positive deer confirmed
properties.description: Published by Minnesota Department of Natural Resources - www.dnr.state.mn.us on 12/21/2009 - With test results for the entire fall sample of hunter-harvested deer in northwestern Minnesota pending, tissue samples from one suspect deer submitted for expedited testing have come back positive for bovine tuberculosis (TB).
